node.text:
Chasing waterfalls with @douglassertao in Brazil, a country home to world-famous waterfalls and stunning natural attractions.

Salto Utiariti waterfall can be found in Campo Novo do Parecis in Mato Grosso. It has an imposing height of 85 meters, urging onlookers to marvel at it in awe! 🇧🇷

What's the tallest waterfall you've ever seen?

Video by @douglassertao

Share your story: #roamtheplanet

node.text:
Photo by @lukekonarzewski, here’s what he had to say about this place: “It took a total of 23 hours on unbelievably windy and bumpy roads to get here. Fighting off motion sickness the entire way. Well worth it to see these incredibly turquoise blue pools hidden deep in the foothills of the Andes. Crazy to think the locals decided to open this place up to tourists just four years ago. Feeling fortunate to have seen this amazing place!”
Share your story: #roamtheplanet
